Counseling Intern", "Research Assistant (Psychology)", "Mental Health Advocate"]}, "title": "Clinical Psychology & Mental Health Counseling", "domains": ["Clinical Practice", "Educational Institutions", "Corporate Wellness", "Rehabilitation Centers"], "evidence": {"values": "Strongly aligns with Meaningful Impact (helping individuals heal) and Relationships (deep client connections). May not fully satisfy Financial Success (though private practice can be lucrative) or Leadership (unless in an administrative role).", "aptitude": "Strong verbal communication (self-rated 4/5) and problem-solving (5/5) are essential for client interaction and treatment planning. Lack of formal scores is a hurdle for the rigorous academic path.", "interest": "Inferred ''S'' (Social) and ''I'' (Investigative) types are central to understanding human behavior and applying therapeutic techniques.", "knowledge": "General knowledge of human behavior and society is a good starting point, but specialized knowledge in psychology will be built in college.", "personality": "High agreeableness (4.0) is perfect for empathetic client relationships. Low neuroticism (2.5) is crucial for handling clients'' emotional distress. Moderate extraversion (3.8) helps in building rapport.", "employability": "Excellent communication and teamwork skills are vital. Adaptability and professionalism are key for handling diverse cases. Leadership skills are less critical for clinical roles."}, "whyItFits": "This path is worth exploring due to its strong alignment with the student''s altruistic values and interpersonal strengths. It offers a stable, respected career with autonomy. The student should explore it through volunteering or introductory courses to see if the day-to-day work resonates.", "matchScore": 65, "description": "This field directly addresses the student''s value of meaningful impact and leverages their high agreeableness and problem-solving skills. It offers autonomy in private practice and stable income. However, it requires extensive academic training and may not align as strongly with the desire for high financial rewards or broad leadership roles outside of clinical settings.", "collegeMajors": ["BA/B.Sc in Psychology", "MBBS (followed by MD in Psychiatry)", "Master''s in Counseling Psychology (after bachelor''s)"], "entranceExams": ["NEET (for MBBS + MD Psychiatry)", "CUET (for BA/B.Sc Psychology)", "University-specific psychology entrance tests"], "preparationFocus": "Volunteer at a helpline or NGO. Read introductory psychology texts. Focus on Biology and English for NEET/medical paths, or Humanities subjects for psychology degrees."}], "specificOptions": {"highFit": [{"name": "Social Entrepreneur", "salary": {"max": 20, "min": 6}}, {"name": "Impact Investment Analyst", "salary": {"max": 18, "min": 8}}, {"name": "Product Manager (Social Tech)", "salary": {"max": 25, "min": 10}}], "mediumFit": [{"name": "Business Analyst (Tech)", "salary": {"max": 12, "min": 6}}, {"name": "UX Researcher", "salary": {"max": 10, "min": 5}}], "exploreLater": [{"name": "Clinical Psychologist", "salary": {"max": 15, "min": 5}}, {"name": "School Counselor", "salary": {"max": 8, "min": 4}}]}}', '{"priorityA": [{"skill": "Quantitative & Abstract Reasoning", "whyNeeded": "Essential for clearing entrance exams (JEE, CAT, CUET) and succeeding in any business or tech-related career. Critical for financial modeling, data analysis, and logical decision-making.", "howToBuild": "1. Enroll in online courses (Khan Academy, Brilliant.org) for foundational math and logic. 2. Practice daily with past papers of target entrance exams. 3. Use apps like Lumosity for brain training. 4. Seek a tutor for personalized guidance if needed.", "targetLevel": 4, "currentLevel": 1}], "priorityB": [{"skill": "Leadership & Project Management", "whyNeeded": "To transition from individual contributor to leader, crucial for entrepreneurship and senior roles. Aligns with the student''s high motivation for leadership.", "howToBuild": "1. Lead a school club or community project. 2. Take online courses on Coursera (e.g., ''Leading People and Teams''). 3. Practice by organizing events or initiatives. 4. Seek mentorship from a local entrepreneur or professional.", "targetLevel": 4, "currentLevel": 2}], "learningTracks": [{"track": "Business & Social Impact", "topics": "Microeconomics, Financial Accounting, Social Innovation, Business Communication, Basic Coding (Python)", "suggestedIf": "You are drawn to social entrepreneurship and leadership."}, {"track": "Technology & Product", "topics": "Programming Fundamentals, Data Structures, User-Centered Design, Agile Methodology, Statistics", "suggestedIf": "You enjoy building digital solutions and managing projects."}, {"track": "Psychology & Counseling", "topics": "Introduction to Psychology, Research Methods, Developmental Psychology, Counseling Techniques, Ethics", "suggestedIf": "You are deeply interested in human behavior and helping others."}], "currentStrengths": ["Problem Solving", "Digital Fluency", "Communication", "Teamwork"], "recommendedTrack": "Business & Social Impact. This track best synthesizes your values of financial success, leadership, and meaningful impact, and leverages your general stream background and strong soft skills."}', '{"projects": [{"steps": ["Define the problem and scope", "Conduct secondary research and interviews", "Brainstorm solutions", "Develop a prototype", "Present findings to peers/teachers"], "title": "Social Issue Analysis & Solution Proposal", "output": "A written report, a presentation deck, and a prototype link.", "skills": ["Problem Solving", "Research", "Communication", "Digital Fluency"], "purpose": "Demonstrates initiative, analytical thinking, and alignment with social impact values. A strong portfolio piece for college applications.", "timeline": "2-3 months", "resources": ["Google Scholar", "Local NGO contacts", "Figma (free tier)", "Canva for presentations"], "difficulty": "Interm